00:05:39.920 --> 00:05:41.760
You can tell that
identical fermions do not

00:05:41.760 --> 00:05:43.720
want to be the same state,
and identical bosons

00:05:43.720 --> 00:05:46.760
do as we saw last time,
as an extra factor of two

00:05:46.760 --> 00:05:49.390
for two particles that are
actually n for n particles.

00:05:49.390 --> 00:05:51.281
So bosons want to be
in the same state.

00:05:51.281 --> 00:05:53.030
Fermions want to not
be in the same state,

00:05:53.030 --> 00:05:54.210
so if we just look
at the world and say,

00:05:54.210 --> 00:05:56.130
which particles are
well modeled by assuming

00:05:56.130 --> 00:05:57.830
we have bosons, which
particles are well

00:05:57.830 --> 00:05:59.460
modeled by assuming
we have fermions.

00:05:59.460 --> 00:06:02.660
And answer turns out to be the
following, any particle that

00:06:02.660 --> 00:06:05.250
has intrinsic angular momentum,
which is a half integer,

00:06:05.250 --> 00:06:07.780
any particle which
spin like the electron,

00:06:07.780 --> 00:06:09.390
which has a limit
to 1/2 and we'll

00:06:09.390 --> 00:06:11.980
study that in more detail
later, any particle that

00:06:11.980 --> 00:06:17.080
has half-integer intrinsic
angular momentum empirically

00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:18.196
turns out to be a fermion.

00:06:18.196 --> 00:06:20.070
Take two electrons, take
their wave function,

00:06:20.070 --> 00:06:22.000
and swap the positions
of the two electrons,

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:23.708
the way function picks
up the minus sign.

00:06:23.708 --> 00:06:25.816
Take two neutrons,
also spin 1/2.

00:06:25.816 --> 00:06:27.440
Swap them and you
pick up a minus sign.

00:06:27.440 --> 00:06:28.420
It's a fermion.

00:06:28.420 --> 00:06:30.130
Take two particles of
light, two photons,

00:06:30.130 --> 00:06:32.120
swap them and you
get a plus sign,

00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:33.690
and these guys
have integer spin.

00:06:33.690 --> 00:06:37.636
Angular momentum of light
is 1, and similarly,

00:06:37.636 --> 00:06:39.010
if we could, for
the Higgs boson,

00:06:39.010 --> 00:06:40.801
if you take two Higgs
bosons and swap them,

00:06:40.801 --> 00:06:42.430
you'll discover
that they're bosons

00:06:42.430 --> 00:06:46.120
and as a consequence there's
a plus sign under exchange.

00:06:46.120 --> 00:06:48.780
So that is not
surprising, it's just

00:06:48.780 --> 00:06:50.500
an observable
property of the world.

00:06:50.500 --> 00:06:53.440
The thing that's shocking
is why that's true, right?

00:06:53.440 --> 00:06:55.630
Why is it that things that
have half-integer angular

00:06:55.630 --> 00:06:59.031
momentum, which sounds like
an independent property

00:06:59.031 --> 00:07:01.530
from whether they're bosonic
or whether identical bosons are

00:07:01.530 --> 00:07:03.071
identified, why is
it that all things

00:07:03.071 --> 00:07:06.640
with half-integer angular
momentum or spin are fermions,

00:07:06.640 --> 00:07:09.730
and all things with integer
angular momentum like light

00:07:09.730 --> 00:07:15.620
or the Higgs boson or
me we're for bosonic,

00:07:15.620 --> 00:07:18.250
we're identical
with an even sign,

00:07:18.250 --> 00:07:20.500
and that requires
quantum field theory.

00:07:20.500 --> 00:07:24.100
But it's not insanely difficult.

00:07:24.100 --> 00:07:26.765
It requires the bearest minima
of quantum field theory.

00:07:26.765 --> 00:07:27.770
So anyone who wants
to understand,

00:07:27.770 --> 00:07:29.710
