00:07:51.280 --> 00:07:51.780
Ah-ha.

00:07:51.780 --> 00:07:54.650
There must be an
extra quantum number

00:07:54.650 --> 00:07:57.834
and on top of that, so the
spin, the two possible states

00:07:57.834 --> 00:07:58.500
of the electron.

00:07:58.500 --> 00:08:00.420
And secondly, it must
be that electrons

00:08:00.420 --> 00:08:01.679
can't be in the same state.

00:08:01.679 --> 00:08:03.345
So it sounds like
that's two hypotheses.

00:08:03.345 --> 00:08:05.650
Now, if you take
those two hypotheses,

00:08:05.650 --> 00:08:06.840
everything else follows.

00:08:06.840 --> 00:08:07.890
Fine.

00:08:07.890 --> 00:08:09.830
What Dirac discovered
when he studied

00:08:09.830 --> 00:08:12.590
the relativistic version of
the Schrodinger equation, which

00:08:12.590 --> 00:08:14.350
really is quantum
field theory, but when

00:08:14.350 --> 00:08:15.808
he studied the
relativistic version

00:08:15.808 --> 00:08:19.802
of electrons, quantum
mechanical relativistic version,

00:08:19.802 --> 00:08:21.760
he discovered that these
two things are linked.

00:08:26.470 --> 00:08:27.350
It is cool.

00:08:27.350 --> 00:08:27.851
I grant you.

00:08:27.851 --> 00:08:30.100
So you he discovered that
these two things are linked,

00:08:30.100 --> 00:08:32.200
and he identified what's
referred to as the spin

00:08:32.200 --> 00:08:33.146
statistics theorem.

00:08:33.146 --> 00:08:35.270
If you know the spin, you
determine the statistics.

00:08:35.270 --> 00:08:36.799
So exactly how that
works, that does

00:08:36.799 --> 00:08:38.424
require a little bit
of effort-- that's

00:08:38.424 --> 00:08:41.679
the 15 minutes-- but you can
dispense with that entirely

00:08:41.679 --> 00:08:45.000
and not be at all shocked by
anything if you just accept

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:50.300
two principles instead of
one, first, that electrons are

00:08:50.300 --> 00:08:53.220
anti-fermionic, so they don't
want to be the same state,

00:08:53.220 --> 00:08:56.028
and secondly, they
have half-integer spin.

